Duties

                                        Major duties include, but are not limited to:

Utilizes a computer to enter and retrieve basic information;
Utilizes dietetic software programs to retrieve diet orders, recipes, and menu and inventory data;
Prints and assembles packets;
Properly operates telephone equipment to transfer or place calls on hold;
Provides professional and courteous customer service;
Triages telephone calls from customers and/or patients;
Provides basic-level education and information on therapeutic diets to patients, guests, and nursing staff;
Resolves customer and/or patient complaints;
Utilizes knowledge of basic and routine modified diets to identify problems in diet order information and take appropriate corrective action;
Correctly interprets diet activity and patient information, to ensure appropriate food items on meals trays;
Verifies physician orders for unusual diets, conflicting modifications, tube feeding orders and nutritional supplements;
Assist with food selections, ensuring appropriateness of menu selections for complex diets;
Answers the telephone using proper business etiquette;
Communicates with customers in a pleasant, friendly, personable, and professional manner;
Communicates effectively via telephone and in-person;
Attends to both verbal and nonverbal aspects of communication.

Work Schedule: Full-Time/5 days per week/Shift will be determined during the interview.
Compressed/Flexible:  Not Available
Telework: Not Available
Virtual: This is not a virtual position.
Position Description/PD#: Health Technician (Dietetic)/PD99796S
Relocation/Recruitment Incentives: Not Authorized
Permanent Change of Station (PCS): Not Authorized
PCS Appraised Value Offer (AVO): Not Authorized
Financial Disclosure Report: Not required


This is a LUINA Bargaining Unit Position.
This position is covered by locality-based comparability pay.
May be required to attend conferences at other facilities or other VA sites on occasion.
Veterans' preference in hiring does not apply when selecting individuals under VA's Direct Hire Authority. When hiring under Direct Hire Authority, the law allows selecting officials to hire applicants without regard to 5 U.S.C. 3309-3318, which eliminates the requirement for applying Veterans' preference. VA HR Offices may assess and select any qualified applicant in the order applicants are received.

 Help

Duties

                                        Information Technology Specialists are valued members of our team.  As an IT Specialist, you will serve as an information technology programmer providing technical guidance in designing, coding, processing, testing, installing, and maintaining computer processes needed to evaluate and manage all phases of regional SSA management/administrative operations via computer systems.

Selectee will serve as an IT Specialist evaluating, developing, and implementing software using programming languages and command language. Will be expected to generate new programs and/or modify existing programs using programming and database management system languages.

Our programmer teams design, develop, maintain, document, and support workload control, processing, and administrative software applications. We provide the full range of electronic data processing, procedures, design, and technology to meet the management and administrative needs of SSA components in the Nation.  We maintain our portfolio of over 70 web-based and client server applications, and over 300 mainframe jobs to support various components.  

Expectations include:

providing agile application project management, writing and maintaining computer programs, descriptive documentation, and operating instructions;
defining user needs, suggesting new computer applications and automated processes, reviewing proposals for major projects, special studies or computer programming requests;
working with users of SSA's systems (e.g. mainframe, personal computer, local area network) in the formulation of requirements that result in modification to the system and maintenance of all regional software programs;
coding, testing, debugging and documenting programs;
being responsible for the overall effectiveness and efficiency of the software applications and data processing systems, and working with other team members and national developers to fully integrate all segments of a project.

Programming is done in any of several languages that may include .NET, .Net Core, C#, ColdFusion, JavaScript, JQuery, JAVA, JCL, AJAX, WebSphere, or Microsoft SQL. Knowledge of tools such as Dreamweaver, Visual Studio, Team Foundation Server, Azure DevOps, and GIT are desired.

Skill and/or experience with .NET/.NET Core is a key skill we are looking for.

